Imagine the ideal designer dog. It would be smart, healthy and hypoallergenic. It would have the yap bred out and longevity bred in. And, most important, it would never lose its puppy face.

Enter the 'cava-poo-chon.' The breed is the newest and latest in the decades-old search for the dog-face fountain of youth and perfect pet accessory.

But the American Kennel Club does not recognize the new trend as an official breed, and one expert calls some specially bred small dogs expensive 'gimmicks.'

