'I have been blown away,' said Bradshaw, who also hired Haynes as a trainer. 'She is amazing, the cutest puppy I've ever seen.'

Bradshaw flies frequently for her job as a technology saleswoman, and she leaves Bridgette at day care, where the ten-pounder is a favorite.

'Every time I log in, she is running around having a blast,' Bradshaw said. She sometimes feels like Bridgette has forgotten about her until pick-up time, when Bridgette spots Bradshaw and 'runs full-speed ahead, her tail going a million miles a minute, right into my arms.'

